---
/**
 * ai-agents/0003 · Figure 4 — "Three MCP primitives" (M6: Tools / Resources /
 * Prompts → MCP Server).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/ai-agents/lessons/0003-how-coding-agents-work.html.
 * Kept as an .astro component (not inline MDX) so the kebab-case SVG attributes
 * render byte-for-byte. marker-end url(#arw) references the shared <defs>
 * arrowheads emitted once in the MDX body.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 560 160"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Three MCP primitives: Tools, Resources, and Prompts all connecting up to a single MCP Server box"
    >
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <!-- MCP Server at top -->
            <rect
                x="180"
                y="10"
                width="200"
                height="32"
                rx="5"
                fill="#f1eee2"
                stroke="#7a1f12"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text
                x="280"
                y="30"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                fill="#111110"
                font-weight="600">MCP Server</text
            >

            <!-- Tools -->
            <rect
                x="20"
                y="90"
                width="160"
                height="56"
                rx="5"
                fill="#f1eee2"
                stroke="#7a1f12"
                stroke-width="1.3"></rect>
            <text
                x="100"
                y="108"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                fill="#111110"
                font-weight="600">Tools</text
            >
            <text x="100" y="122" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >Functions the agent can call:</text
            >
            <text x="100" y="134" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >check_invoice, send_email,</text
            >
            <text x="100" y="146" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f">query_db</text>

            <!-- Resources -->
            <rect
                x="200"
                y="90"
                width="160"
                height="56"
                rx="5"
                fill="#eef5ee"
                stroke="#2f5d3a"
                stroke-width="1.3"></rect>
            <text
                x="280"
                y="108"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                fill="#111110"
                font-weight="600">Resources</text
            >
            <text x="280" y="122" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >Data the agent can read:</text
            >
            <text x="280" y="134" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >file:// URLs, database</text
            >
            <text x="280" y="146" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >records, config</text
            >

            <!-- Prompts -->
            <rect
                x="380"
                y="90"
                width="160"
                height="56"
                rx="5"
                fill="#eef2f5"
                stroke="#1f3a5a"
                stroke-width="1.3"></rect>
            <text
                x="460"
                y="108"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                fill="#111110"
                font-weight="600">Prompts</text
            >
            <text x="460" y="122" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >Pre-built templates:</text
            >
            <text x="460" y="134" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >'summarize this ticket',</text
            >
            <text x="460" y="146" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >'draft reply'</text
            >

            <!-- Arrows from primitives up to MCP Server -->
            <line
                x1="100"
                y1="90"
                x2="215"
                y2="42"
                stroke="#6b675f"
                stroke-width="1.3"
                marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <line
                x1="280"
                y1="90"
                x2="280"
                y2="42"
                stroke="#6b675f"
                stroke-width="1.3"
                marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <line
                x1="460"
                y1="90"
                x2="350"
                y2="42"
                stroke="#6b675f"
                stroke-width="1.3"
                marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        An MCP server can expose all three primitives. Most start with Tools only; Resources and
        Prompts are for richer agent-server integration.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
